>I completely agree with Dan on this issue.  (No, it's not the first
>time...)  One of my biggest gripes against the Orange Books is that
>it doesn't require a secure attention key until B2, while I think it
>should be mandatory in B1, and maybe even C2.

Secure attention keys work only with closed systems or trusted terminals.
These account for such a small part of the world as not to be
interesting.  My problem with the Orange book is that it is too archaic
to recognize this.  

